          "date": "2014-12-29 17:20:46.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-5408 fid: cleanup fid_is_*() names and uses",
        "message": "LU-5408 fid: cleanup fid_is_*() names and uses\n\nIn fid_is_md_operative() return false for FIDs with seq\nFID_SEQ_OST_MDT0 (because these are OST FIDs).\n\nRename fid_seq_is_mdt0() to fid_seq_is_ost_mdt0() and fid_is_mdt0() to\nfid_is_ost_mdt0().  Rename fid_seq_is_default() to\nfid_seq_is_lov_default(). Remove the confusing or redundant functions\nfid_seq_is_mdt(), fid_seq_is_dot_lustre(), and fid_is_internal().  The\n*is_mdt* names may have made sense before DNE but are just confusing\nnow.\n\nRemove FID policy from some utilities. In lhsmtool_posix.c remove\nfid_is_file(). In liblustreapi.c and lustre_rsync.c remove calls to\nfid_is_sane(fid). Move fid_is_sane() out of lustre_idl.h and into\nlustre_fid.h as a way of sending a message about who should and who\nshould not be using this function.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Idb655927f7ff05fb6c860b00ebaa7beacb490614\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
